@GigaLigma No the percentages your talking about are just women in the military. Special forces are units like the Navy seals and SAS, SBS. 

No women have made it through selection for the Navy seals and it wasn’t till 2021 before two women even attempted SAS selection. No information I could find regarding if they passed or not. Out of 100 men only 1 or 2 makes it through. 

Nothing sexist about it you’re just ignorant to the truth of the matter. You’re not intelligent. Granted some women work with these teams but that’s normally CST or cultural support teams. There is a difference with special forces and intelligence officers. Maybe do your own research before you act like the smartest person in the room 😉

